    "description": "The strategy is a single name, long only momentum and trend confirmation model in US equities, designed to participate in sustained upside moves while avoiding weak or non directional regimes. It trades Tesla (TSLA) using daily data and generates a bullish signal when three conditions align: intermediate momentum is positive (14 day RSI above a mild threshold), trend direction is positive (MACD line above its signal), and trend strength is non trivial (14 day ADX above a minimum). This combinati",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a single name, long only momentum and trend confirmation model in US equities, designed to participate in sustained upside moves while avoiding weak or non directional regimes. It trades Tesla (TSLA) using daily data and generates a bullish signal when three conditions align: intermediate momentum is positive (14 day RSI above a mild threshold), trend direction is positive (MACD line above its signal), and trend strength is non trivial (14 day ADX above a minimum). This combination targets environments where TSLA is exhibiting improving upside momentum with sufficient trend persistence, seeking to capture medium term continuation rather than mean reversion.\n\nWhen the conditions are met, the model issues a long insight with a 5 trading day horizon and only one signal per day, implying entries are evaluated once per session after indicators are warmed up. Portfolio construction allocates equally across active insights, which in practice means full allocation to TSLA when long and otherwise no position. Execution is immediate at signal time. Risk management applies a 1.5 percent trailing stop to limit drawdowns during adverse reversals, with no explicit leverage or volatility scaling beyond the trailing stop.",
